The paper focuses on using a character-level convolutional neural network for semantic classification of tabular data, age prediction from social media posts, and email spam classification. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). However, given the emphasis on language processing and transfer learning, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG and cs.AI.
